      "body" : "ok, I hope that there is a man who knows C + + and ready to implement 2.0 support ))\r\n\r\nNow, if it's possible - let's stop to throw 500 http error for every internal exception.\r\nIt will be the step toward JSON-RPC 2.0 ))\r\n\r\nFor example, if you call method \"getreceivedbyaddress\" and provide wrong address - Bitcoind should return 200 http response and the same message as now (not 500 http error with the message).\r\nIt's the feature that blocks normal use of the Bitcoind by a Java client\r\n",
